HEADWORD: mother-of-thousands
<hw>mother-of-thousands</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An East Asiatic
saxifrage (<spn>Saxifraga stolonifera</spn>) with racemes of small
red-and-white flowers; spreads by numerous creeping stolons; called also
<altname>strawberry geranium</altname> and <altname>strawberry
saxifrage</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> strawberry geranium, strawberry saxifrage,
<spn>Saxifraga stolonifera</spn>, Saxifraga sarmentosam.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mother-of-thyme</ent>⟦br⟧
